name: bigquery
title: BigQuery API
description: A data platform for customers to create, manage, share and query data.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

fields.name: creationTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] The time when this table was created, in milliseconds since the epoch.

fields.name: externalDataConfiguration
fields.desc: [Optional] Describes the data format, location, and other properties of a table stored outside of BigQuery. By defining these properties, the data source can then be queried as if it were a standard BigQuery table.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: [Experimental] The labels associated with this table. You can use these to organize and group your tables. Label keys and values can be no longer than 63 characters, can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. Label values are optional. Label keys must start with a letter and each label in the list must have a different key.

fields.name: lastModifiedTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] The time when this table was last modified, in milliseconds since the epoch.

fields.name: schema
fields.desc: [Optional] Describes the schema of this table.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: [Optional] A user-friendly description of this table.

fields.name: friendlyName
fields.desc: [Optional] A descriptive name for this table.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: [Output-only] A URL that can be used to access this resource again.

fields.name: tableReference
fields.desc: [Required] Reference describing the ID of this table.

fields.name: timePartitioning
fields.desc: [Experimental] If specified, configures time-based partitioning for this table.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: [Output-only] A hash of this resource.

fields.name: expirationTime
fields.desc: [Optional] The time when this table expires, in milliseconds since the epoch. If not present, the table will persist indefinitely. Expired tables will be deleted and their storage reclaimed.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: [Output-only] The geographic location where the table resides. This value is inherited from the dataset.

fields.name: numRows
fields.desc: [Output-only] The number of rows of data in this table, excluding any data in the streaming buffer.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Output-only] Describes the table type. The following values are supported: TABLE: A normal BigQuery table. VIEW: A virtual table defined by a SQL query. EXTERNAL: A table that references data stored in an external storage system, such as Google Cloud Storage. The default value is TABLE.

fields.name: view
fields.desc: [Optional] The view definition.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: [Output-only] An opaque ID uniquely identifying the table.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: [Output-only] The type of the resource.

fields.name: numBytes
fields.desc: [Output-only] The size of this table in bytes, excluding any data in the streaming buffer.

fields.name: numLongTermBytes
fields.desc: [Output-only] The number of bytes in the table that are considered "long-term storage".

fields.name: streamingBuffer
fields.desc: [Output-only] Contains information regarding this table's streaming buffer, if one is present. This field will be absent if the table is not being streamed to or if there is no data in the streaming buffer.

fields.name: insertErrors
fields.desc: An array of errors for rows that were not inserted.

fields.name: errors
fields.desc: Error information for the row indicated by the index property.

fields.name: index
fields.desc: The index of the row that error applies to.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the response.

fields.name: useLegacySql
fields.desc: Specifies whether to use BigQuery's legacy SQL for this view. The default value is true. If set to false, the view will use BigQuery's standard SQL: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/sql-reference/ Queries and views that reference this view must use the same flag value.

fields.name: userDefinedFunctionResources
fields.desc: [Experimental] Describes user-defined function resources used in the query.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: [Required] A query that BigQuery executes when the view is referenced.

fields.name: familyId
fields.desc: Identifier of the column family.

fields.name: onlyReadLatest
fields.desc: [Optional] If this is set only the latest version of value are exposed for all columns in this column family. This can be overridden for a specific column by listing that column in 'columns' and specifying a different setting for that column.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Optional] The type to convert the value in cells of this column family. The values are expected to be encoded using HBase Bytes.toBytes function when using the BINARY encoding value. Following BigQuery types are allowed (case-sensitive) - BYTES STRING INTEGER FLOAT BOOLEAN Default type is BYTES. This can be overridden for a specific column by listing that column in 'columns' and specifying a type for it.

fields.name: columns
fields.desc: [Optional] Lists of columns that should be exposed as individual fields as opposed to a list of (column name, value) pairs. All columns whose qualifier matches a qualifier in this list can be accessed as .. Other columns can be accessed as a list through .Column field.

fields.name: encoding
fields.desc: [Optional] The encoding of the values when the type is not STRING. Acceptable encoding values are: TEXT - indicates values are alphanumeric text strings. BINARY - indicates values are encoded using HBase Bytes.toBytes family of functions. This can be overridden for a specific column by listing that column in 'columns' and specifying an encoding for it.

fields.name: columnFamilies
fields.desc: [Optional] List of column families to expose in the table schema along with their types. This list restricts the column families that can be referenced in queries and specifies their value types. You can use this list to do type conversions - see the 'type' field for more details. If you leave this list empty, all column families are present in the table schema and their values are read as BYTES. During a query only the column families referenced in that query are read from Bigtable.

fields.name: ignoreUnspecifiedColumnFamilies
fields.desc: [Optional] If field is true, then the column families that are not specified in columnFamilies list are not exposed in the table schema. Otherwise, they are read with BYTES type values. The default value is false.

fields.name: readRowkeyAsString
fields.desc: [Optional] If field is true, then the rowkey column families will be read and converted to string. Otherwise they are read with BYTES type values and users need to manually cast them with CAST if necessary. The default value is false.

fields.name: allowJaggedRows
fields.desc: [Optional] Indicates if BigQuery should accept rows that are missing trailing optional columns. If true, BigQuery treats missing trailing columns as null values. If false, records with missing trailing columns are treated as bad records, and if there are too many bad records, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is false.

fields.name: allowQuotedNewlines
fields.desc: [Optional] Indicates if BigQuery should allow quoted data sections that contain newline characters in a CSV file. The default value is false.

fields.name: encoding
fields.desc: [Optional] The character encoding of the data. The supported values are UTF-8 or ISO-8859-1. The default value is UTF-8. BigQuery decodes the data after the raw, binary data has been split using the values of the quote and fieldDelimiter properties.

fields.name: fieldDelimiter
fields.desc: [Optional] The separator for fields in a CSV file. BigQuery converts the string to ISO-8859-1 encoding, and then uses the first byte of the encoded string to split the data in its raw, binary state. BigQuery also supports the escape sequence "\t" to specify a tab separator. The default value is a comma (',').

fields.name: quote
fields.desc: [Optional] The value that is used to quote data sections in a CSV file. BigQuery converts the string to ISO-8859-1 encoding, and then uses the first byte of the encoded string to split the data in its raw, binary state. The default value is a double-quote ('"'). If your data does not contain quoted sections, set the property value to an empty string. If your data contains quoted newline characters, you must also set the allowQuotedNewlines property to true.

fields.name: skipLeadingRows
fields.desc: [Optional] The number of rows at the top of a CSV file that BigQuery will skip when reading the data. The default value is 0. This property is useful if you have header rows in the file that should be skipped.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: [Optional] If unset, this is a positional parameter. Otherwise, should be unique within a query.

fields.name: parameterType
fields.desc: [Required] The type of this parameter.

fields.name: parameterValue
fields.desc: [Required] The value of this parameter.

fields.name: estimatedBytes
fields.desc: [Output-only] A lower-bound estimate of the number of bytes currently in the streaming buffer.

fields.name: estimatedRows
fields.desc: [Output-only] A lower-bound estimate of the number of rows currently in the streaming buffer.

fields.name: oldestEntryTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] Contains the timestamp of the oldest entry in the streaming buffer, in milliseconds since the epoch, if the streaming buffer is available.

fields.name: schema
fields.desc: The schema of the results. Present only when the query completes successfully.

fields.name: cacheHit
fields.desc: Whether the query result was fetched from the query cache.

fields.name: errors
fields.desc: [Output-only] All errors and warnings encountered during the running of the job. Errors here do not necessarily mean that the job has completed or was unsuccessful.

fields.name: jobComplete
fields.desc: Whether the query has completed or not. If rows or totalRows are present, this will always be true. If this is false, totalRows will not be available.

fields.name: jobReference
fields.desc: Reference to the BigQuery Job that was created to run the query. This field will be present even if the original request timed out, in which case GetQueryResults can be used to read the results once the query has completed. Since this API only returns the first page of results, subsequent pages can be fetched via the same mechanism (GetQueryResults).

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the response.

fields.name: numDmlAffectedRows
fields.desc: [Output-only, Experimental] The number of rows affected by a DML statement. Present only for DML statements INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE.

fields.name: pageToken
fields.desc: A token used for paging results.

fields.name: totalBytesProcessed
fields.desc: The total number of bytes processed for this query.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: A hash of this response.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: An object with as many results as can be contained within the maximum permitted reply size. To get any additional rows, you can call GetQueryResults and specify the jobReference returned above. Present only when the query completes successfully.

fields.name: totalRows
fields.desc: The total number of rows in the complete query result set, which can be more than the number of rows in this single page of results. Present only when the query completes successfully.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: [Output-only] Opaque ID field of the job

fields.name: jobReference
fields.desc: [Optional] Reference describing the unique-per-user name of the job.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: [Output-only] The type of the resource.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: [Output-only] A URL that can be used to access this resource again.

fields.name: statistics
fields.desc: [Output-only] Information about the job, including starting time and ending time of the job.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: [Output-only] The status of this job. Examine this value when polling an asynchronous job to see if the job is complete.

fields.name: configuration
fields.desc: [Required] Describes the job configuration.

fields.name: user_email
fields.desc: [Output-only] Email address of the user who ran the job.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: [Output-only] A hash of this resource.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: A hash of this page of results.

fields.name: jobs
fields.desc: List of jobs that were requested.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique opaque ID of the job.

fields.name: jobReference
fields.desc: Job reference uniquely identifying the job.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: Running state of the job. When the state is DONE, errorResult can be checked to determine whether the job succeeded or failed.

fields.name: configuration
fields.desc: [Full-projection-only] Specifies the job configuration.

fields.name: errorResult
fields.desc: A result object that will be present only if the job has failed.

fields.name: statistics
fields.desc: [Output-only] Information about the job, including starting time and ending time of the job.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: [Full-projection-only] Describes the state of the job.

fields.name: user_email
fields.desc: [Full-projection-only] Email address of the user who ran the job.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the response.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: A token to request the next page of results.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: A hash of the page of results

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The type of list.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: A token to request the next page of results.

fields.name: projects
fields.desc: Projects to which you have at least READ access.

fields.name: friendlyName
fields.desc: A descriptive name for this project.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: An opaque ID of this project.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type.

fields.name: numericId
fields.desc: The numeric ID of this project.

fields.name: projectReference
fields.desc: A unique reference to this project.

fields.name: totalItems
fields.desc: The total number of projects in the list.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Required] The field data type. Possible values include STRING, BYTES, INTEGER, INT64 (same as INTEGER), FLOAT, FLOAT64 (same as FLOAT), BOOLEAN, BOOL (same as BOOLEAN), TIMESTAMP, DATE, TIME, DATETIME, RECORD (where RECORD indicates that the field contains a nested schema) or STRUCT (same as RECORD).

fields.name: description
fields.desc: [Optional] The field description. The maximum length is 16K characters.

fields.name: fields
fields.desc: [Optional] Describes the nested schema fields if the type property is set to RECORD.

fields.name: mode
fields.desc: [Optional] The field mode. Possible values include NULLABLE, REQUIRED and REPEATED. The default value is NULLABLE.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: [Required] The field name. The name must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), or underscores (_), and must start with a letter or underscore. The maximum length is 128 characters.

fields.name: job
fields.desc: The final state of the job.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the response.

fields.name: schema
fields.desc: [Optional] The schema for the destination table. The schema can be omitted if the destination table already exists, or if you're loading data from Google Cloud Datastore.

fields.name: sourceFormat
fields.desc: [Optional] The format of the data files. For CSV files, specify "CSV". For datastore backups, specify "DATASTORE_BACKUP". For newline-delimited JSON, specify "NEWLINE_DELIMITED_JSON". For Avro, specify "AVRO". The default value is CSV.

fields.name: createDisposition
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies whether the job is allowed to create new tables. The following values are supported: CREATE_IF_NEEDED: If the table does not exist, BigQuery creates the table. CREATE_NEVER: The table must already exist. If it does not, a 'notFound' error is returned in the job result. The default value is CREATE_IF_NEEDED. Creation, truncation and append actions occur as one atomic update upon job completion.

fields.name: destinationTable
fields.desc: [Required] The destination table to load the data into.

fields.name: projectionFields
fields.desc: [Experimental] If sourceFormat is set to "DATASTORE_BACKUP", indicates which entity properties to load into BigQuery from a Cloud Datastore backup. Property names are case sensitive and must be top-level properties. If no properties are specified, BigQuery loads all properties. If any named property isn't found in the Cloud Datastore backup, an invalid error is returned in the job result.

fields.name: schemaInline
fields.desc: [Deprecated] The inline schema. For CSV schemas, specify as "Field1:Type1[,Field2:Type2]*". For example, "foo:STRING, bar:INTEGER, baz:FLOAT".

fields.name: schemaUpdateOptions
fields.desc: [Experimental] Allows the schema of the desitination table to be updated as a side effect of the load job. Schema update options are supported in two cases: when writeDisposition is WRITE_APPEND; when writeDisposition is WRITE_TRUNCATE and the destination table is a partition of a table, specified by partition decorators. For normal tables, WRITE_TRUNCATE will always overwrite the schema. One or more of the following values are specified: ALLOW_FIELD_ADDITION: allow adding a nullable field to the schema. ALLOW_FIELD_RELAXATION: allow relaxing a required field in the original schema to nullable.

fields.name: fieldDelimiter
fields.desc: [Optional] The separator for fields in a CSV file. The separator can be any ISO-8859-1 single-byte character. To use a character in the range 128-255, you must encode the character as UTF8. BigQuery converts the string to ISO-8859-1 encoding, and then uses the first byte of the encoded string to split the data in its raw, binary state. BigQuery also supports the escape sequence "\t" to specify a tab separator. The default value is a comma (',').

fields.name: maxBadRecords
fields.desc: [Optional] The maximum number of bad records that BigQuery can ignore when running the job. If the number of bad records exceeds this value, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is 0, which requires that all records are valid.

fields.name: nullMarker
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies a string that represents a null value in a CSV file. For example, if you specify "\N", BigQuery interprets "\N" as a null value when loading a CSV file. The default value is the empty string. If you set this property to a custom value, BigQuery still interprets the empty string as a null value for all data types except for STRING and BYTE. For STRING and BYTE columns, BigQuery interprets the empty string as an empty value.

fields.name: autodetect
fields.desc: [Experimental] Indicates if we should automatically infer the options and schema for CSV and JSON sources.

fields.name: encoding
fields.desc: [Optional] The character encoding of the data. The supported values are UTF-8 or ISO-8859-1. The default value is UTF-8. BigQuery decodes the data after the raw, binary data has been split using the values of the quote and fieldDelimiter properties.

fields.name: quote
fields.desc: [Optional] The value that is used to quote data sections in a CSV file. BigQuery converts the string to ISO-8859-1 encoding, and then uses the first byte of the encoded string to split the data in its raw, binary state. The default value is a double-quote ('"'). If your data does not contain quoted sections, set the property value to an empty string. If your data contains quoted newline characters, you must also set the allowQuotedNewlines property to true.

fields.name: schemaInlineFormat
fields.desc: [Deprecated] The format of the schemaInline property.

fields.name: skipLeadingRows
fields.desc: [Optional] The number of rows at the top of a CSV file that BigQuery will skip when loading the data. The default value is 0. This property is useful if you have header rows in the file that should be skipped.

fields.name: sourceUris
fields.desc: [Required] The fully-qualified URIs that point to your data in Google Cloud Storage. Each URI can contain one '*' wildcard character and it must come after the 'bucket' name.

fields.name: writeDisposition
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies the action that occurs if the destination table already exists. The following values are supported: WRITE_TRUNCATE: If the table already exists, BigQuery overwrites the table data. WRITE_APPEND: If the table already exists, BigQuery appends the data to the table. WRITE_EMPTY: If the table already exists and contains data, a 'duplicate' error is returned in the job result. The default value is WRITE_APPEND. Each action is atomic and only occurs if BigQuery is able to complete the job successfully. Creation, truncation and append actions occur as one atomic update upon job completion.

fields.name: allowJaggedRows
fields.desc: [Optional] Accept rows that are missing trailing optional columns. The missing values are treated as nulls. If false, records with missing trailing columns are treated as bad records, and if there are too many bad records, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is false. Only applicable to CSV, ignored for other formats.

fields.name: allowQuotedNewlines
fields.desc: Indicates if BigQuery should allow quoted data sections that contain newline characters in a CSV file. The default value is false.

fields.name: ignoreUnknownValues
fields.desc: [Optional] Indicates if BigQuery should allow extra values that are not represented in the table schema. If true, the extra values are ignored. If false, records with extra columns are treated as bad records, and if there are too many bad records, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is false. The sourceFormat property determines what BigQuery treats as an extra value: CSV: Trailing columns JSON: Named values that don't match any column names

fields.name: query
fields.desc: [Output-only] Statistics for a query job.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] Start time of this job, in milliseconds since the epoch. This field will be present when the job transitions from the PENDING state to either RUNNING or DONE.

fields.name: totalBytesProcessed
fields.desc: [Output-only] [Deprecated] Use the bytes processed in the query statistics instead.

fields.name: creationTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] Creation time of this job, in milliseconds since the epoch. This field will be present on all jobs.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] End time of this job, in milliseconds since the epoch. This field will be present whenever a job is in the DONE state.

fields.name: extract
fields.desc: [Output-only] Statistics for an extract job.

fields.name: load
fields.desc: [Output-only] Statistics for a load job.

fields.name: jobReference
fields.desc: Reference to the Job that was created to run the query. This field will be present even if the original request timed out, in which case GetQueryResults can be used to read the results once the query has completed. Since this API only returns the first page of results, subsequent pages can be fetched via the same mechanism (GetQueryResults).

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type.

fields.name: numDmlAffectedRows
fields.desc: [Output-only, Experimental] The number of rows affected by a DML statement. Present only for DML statements INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE.

fields.name: pageToken
fields.desc: A token used for paging results.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: An object with as many results as can be contained within the maximum permitted reply size. To get any additional rows, you can call GetQueryResults and specify the jobReference returned above.

fields.name: cacheHit
fields.desc: Whether the query result was fetched from the query cache.

fields.name: errors
fields.desc: [Output-only] All errors and warnings encountered during the running of the job. Errors here do not necessarily mean that the job has completed or was unsuccessful.

fields.name: jobComplete
fields.desc: Whether the query has completed or not. If rows or totalRows are present, this will always be true. If this is false, totalRows will not be available.

fields.name: schema
fields.desc: The schema of the results. Present only when the query completes successfully.

fields.name: totalBytesProcessed
fields.desc: The total number of bytes processed for this query. If this query was a dry run, this is the number of bytes that would be processed if the query were run.

fields.name: totalRows
fields.desc: The total number of rows in the complete query result set, which can be more than the number of rows in this single page of results.

fields.name: structTypes
fields.desc: [Optional] The types of the fields of this struct, in order, if this is a struct.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Required] The type of this field.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: [Optional] Human-oriented description of the field.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: [Optional] The name of this field.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Required] The top level type of this field.

fields.name: arrayType
fields.desc: [Optional] The type of the array's elements, if this is an array.

fields.name: ignoreUnknownValues
fields.desc: [Optional] Accept rows that contain values that do not match the schema. The unknown values are ignored. Default is false, which treats unknown values as errors.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the response.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: The rows to insert.

fields.name: insertId
fields.desc: [Optional] A unique ID for each row. BigQuery uses this property to detect duplicate insertion requests on a best-effort basis.

fields.name: json
fields.desc: [Required] A JSON object that contains a row of data. The object's properties and values must match the destination table's schema.

fields.name: skipInvalidRows
fields.desc: [Optional] Insert all valid rows of a request, even if invalid rows exist. The default value is false, which causes the entire request to fail if any invalid rows exist.

fields.name: templateSuffix
fields.desc: [Experimental] If specified, treats the destination table as a base template, and inserts the rows into an instance table named "{destination}{templateSuffix}". BigQuery will manage creation of the instance table, using the schema of the base template table. See https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/streaming-data-into-bigquery#template-tables for considerations when working with templates tables.

fields.name: datasets
fields.desc: An array of the dataset resources in the project. Each resource contains basic information. For full information about a particular dataset resource, use the Datasets: get method. This property is omitted when there are no datasets in the project.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type. This property always returns the value "bigquery#dataset".

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: [Experimental] The labels associated with this dataset. You can use these to organize and group your datasets.

fields.name: datasetReference
fields.desc: The dataset reference. Use this property to access specific parts of the dataset's ID, such as project ID or dataset ID.

fields.name: friendlyName
fields.desc: A descriptive name for the dataset, if one exists.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The fully-qualified, unique, opaque ID of the dataset.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: A hash value of the results page. You can use this property to determine if the page has changed since the last request.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The list type. This property always returns the value "bigquery#datasetList".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: A token that can be used to request the next results page. This property is omitted on the final results page.

fields.name: skipLeadingRows
fields.desc: [Optional] The number of rows at the top of a sheet that BigQuery will skip when reading the data. The default value is 0. This property is useful if you have header rows that should be skipped. When autodetect is on, behavior is the following: * skipLeadingRows unspecified - Autodetect tries to detect headers in the first row. If they are not detected, the row is read as data. Otherwise data is read starting from the second row. * skipLeadingRows is 0 - Instructs autodetect that there are no headers and data should be read starting from the first row. * skipLeadingRows = N > 0 - Autodetect skips N-1 rows and tries to detect headers in row N. If headers are not detected, row N is just skipped. Otherwise row N is used to extract column names for the detected schema.

fields.name: load
fields.desc: [Pick one] Configures a load job.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: [Pick one] Configures a query job.

fields.name: copy
fields.desc: [Pick one] Copies a table.

fields.name: dryRun
fields.desc: [Optional] If set, don't actually run this job. A valid query will return a mostly empty response with some processing statistics, while an invalid query will return the same error it would if it wasn't a dry run. Behavior of non-query jobs is undefined.

fields.name: extract
fields.desc: [Pick one] Configures an extract job.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: [Experimental] The labels associated with this job. You can use these to organize and group your jobs. Label keys and values can be no longer than 63 characters, can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. Label values are optional. Label keys must start with a letter and each label in the list must have a different key.

fields.name: jobId
fields.desc: [Required] The ID of the job. The ID must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), or dashes (-). The maximum length is 1,024 characters.

fields.name: projectId
fields.desc: [Required] The ID of the project containing this job.

fields.name: errorResult
fields.desc: [Output-only] Final error result of the job. If present, indicates that the job has completed and was unsuccessful.

fields.name: errors
fields.desc: [Output-only] All errors encountered during the running of the job. Errors here do not necessarily mean that the job has completed or was unsuccessful.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: [Output-only] Running state of the job.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the response.

fields.name: pageToken
fields.desc: A token used for paging results. Providing this token instead of the startIndex parameter can help you retrieve stable results when an underlying table is changing.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: Rows of results.

fields.name: totalRows
fields.desc: The total number of rows in the complete table.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: A hash of this page of results.

fields.name: f
fields.desc: Represents a single row in the result set, consisting of one or more fields.

fields.name: message
fields.desc: A human-readable description of the error.

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: A short error code that summarizes the error.

fields.name: debugInfo
fields.desc: Debugging information. This property is internal to Google and should not be used.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Specifies where the error occurred, if present.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Machine-readable operation type.

fields.name: substeps
fields.desc: Human-readable stage descriptions.

fields.name: ignoreUnknownValues
fields.desc: [Optional] Indicates if BigQuery should allow extra values that are not represented in the table schema. If true, the extra values are ignored. If false, records with extra columns are treated as bad records, and if there are too many bad records, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is false. The sourceFormat property determines what BigQuery treats as an extra value: CSV: Trailing columns JSON: Named values that don't match any column names Google Cloud Bigtable: This setting is ignored. Google Cloud Datastore backups: This setting is ignored. Avro: This setting is ignored.

fields.name: schema
fields.desc: [Optional] The schema for the data. Schema is required for CSV and JSON formats. Schema is disallowed for Google Cloud Bigtable, Cloud Datastore backups, and Avro formats.

fields.name: sourceFormat
fields.desc: [Required] The data format. For CSV files, specify "CSV". For Google sheets, specify "GOOGLE_SHEETS". For newline-delimited JSON, specify "NEWLINE_DELIMITED_JSON". For Avro files, specify "AVRO". For Google Cloud Datastore backups, specify "DATASTORE_BACKUP". [Experimental] For Google Cloud Bigtable, specify "BIGTABLE". Please note that reading from Google Cloud Bigtable is experimental and has to be enabled for your project. Please contact Google Cloud Support to enable this for your project.

fields.name: sourceUris
fields.desc: [Required] The fully-qualified URIs that point to your data in Google Cloud. For Google Cloud Storage URIs: Each URI can contain one '*' wildcard character and it must come after the 'bucket' name. Size limits related to load jobs apply to external data sources. For Google Cloud Bigtable URIs: Exactly one URI can be specified and it has be a fully specified and valid HTTPS URL for a Google Cloud Bigtable table. For Google Cloud Datastore backups, exactly one URI can be specified, and it must end with '.backup_info'. Also, the '*' wildcard character is not allowed.

fields.name: googleSheetsOptions
fields.desc: [Optional] Additional options if sourceFormat is set to GOOGLE_SHEETS.

fields.name: maxBadRecords
fields.desc: [Optional] The maximum number of bad records that BigQuery can ignore when reading data. If the number of bad records exceeds this value, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is 0, which requires that all records are valid. This setting is ignored for Google Cloud Bigtable, Google Cloud Datastore backups and Avro formats.

fields.name: autodetect
fields.desc: [Experimental] Try to detect schema and format options automatically. Any option specified explicitly will be honored.

fields.name: bigtableOptions
fields.desc: [Optional] Additional options if sourceFormat is set to BIGTABLE.

fields.name: compression
fields.desc: [Optional] The compression type of the data source. Possible values include GZIP and NONE. The default value is NONE. This setting is ignored for Google Cloud Bigtable, Google Cloud Datastore backups and Avro formats.

fields.name: csvOptions
fields.desc: Additional properties to set if sourceFormat is set to CSV.

fields.name: defaultDataset
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies the default dataset to use for unqualified table names in the query.

fields.name: flattenResults
fields.desc: [Optional] Flattens all nested and repeated fields in the query results. The default value is true. allowLargeResults must be true if this is set to false.

fields.name: schemaUpdateOptions
fields.desc: [Experimental] Allows the schema of the destination table to be updated as a side effect of the query job. Schema update options are supported in two cases: when writeDisposition is WRITE_APPEND; when writeDisposition is WRITE_TRUNCATE and the destination table is a partition of a table, specified by partition decorators. For normal tables, WRITE_TRUNCATE will always overwrite the schema. One or more of the following values are specified: ALLOW_FIELD_ADDITION: allow adding a nullable field to the schema. ALLOW_FIELD_RELAXATION: allow relaxing a required field in the original schema to nullable.

fields.name: useQueryCache
fields.desc: [Optional] Whether to look for the result in the query cache. The query cache is a best-effort cache that will be flushed whenever tables in the query are modified. Moreover, the query cache is only available when a query does not have a destination table specified. The default value is true.

fields.name: destinationTable
fields.desc: [Optional] Describes the table where the query results should be stored. If not present, a new table will be created to store the results.

fields.name: tableDefinitions
fields.desc: [Optional] If querying an external data source outside of BigQuery, describes the data format, location and other properties of the data source. By defining these properties, the data source can then be queried as if it were a standard BigQuery table.

fields.name: useLegacySql
fields.desc: Specifies whether to use BigQuery's legacy SQL dialect for this query. The default value is true. If set to false, the query will use BigQuery's standard SQL: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/sql-reference/ When useLegacySql is set to false, the values of allowLargeResults and flattenResults are ignored; query will be run as if allowLargeResults is true and flattenResults is false.

fields.name: userDefinedFunctionResources
fields.desc: [Experimental] Describes user-defined function resources used in the query.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: [Required] BigQuery SQL query to execute.

fields.name: queryParameters
fields.desc: Query parameters for standard SQL queries.

fields.name: createDisposition
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies whether the job is allowed to create new tables. The following values are supported: CREATE_IF_NEEDED: If the table does not exist, BigQuery creates the table. CREATE_NEVER: The table must already exist. If it does not, a 'notFound' error is returned in the job result. The default value is CREATE_IF_NEEDED. Creation, truncation and append actions occur as one atomic update upon job completion.

fields.name: maximumBytesBilled
fields.desc: [Optional] Limits the bytes billed for this job. Queries that will have bytes billed beyond this limit will fail (without incurring a charge). If unspecified, this will be set to your project default.

fields.name: parameterMode
fields.desc: [Experimental] Standard SQL only. Set to POSITIONAL to use positional (?) query parameters or to NAMED to use named (@myparam) query parameters in this query.

fields.name: priority
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies a priority for the query. Possible values include INTERACTIVE and BATCH. The default value is INTERACTIVE.

fields.name: allowLargeResults
fields.desc: If true, allows the query to produce arbitrarily large result tables at a slight cost in performance. Requires destinationTable to be set.

fields.name: maximumBillingTier
fields.desc: [Optional] Limits the billing tier for this job. Queries that have resource usage beyond this tier will fail (without incurring a charge). If unspecified, this will be set to your project default.

fields.name: preserveNulls
fields.desc: [Deprecated] This property is deprecated.

fields.name: writeDisposition
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies the action that occurs if the destination table already exists. The following values are supported: WRITE_TRUNCATE: If the table already exists, BigQuery overwrites the table data. WRITE_APPEND: If the table already exists, BigQuery appends the data to the table. WRITE_EMPTY: If the table already exists and contains data, a 'duplicate' error is returned in the job result. The default value is WRITE_EMPTY. Each action is atomic and only occurs if BigQuery is able to complete the job successfully. Creation, truncation and append actions occur as one atomic update upon job completion.

fields.name: defaultDataset
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies the default datasetId and projectId to assume for any unqualified table names in the query. If not set, all table names in the query string must be qualified in the format 'datasetId.tableId'.

fields.name: dryRun
fields.desc: [Optional] If set to true, BigQuery doesn't run the job. Instead, if the query is valid, BigQuery returns statistics about the job such as how many bytes would be processed. If the query is invalid, an error returns. The default value is false.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type of the request.

fields.name: maxResults
fields.desc: [Optional] The maximum number of rows of data to return per page of results. Setting this flag to a small value such as 1000 and then paging through results might improve reliability when the query result set is large. In addition to this limit, responses are also limited to 10 MB. By default, there is no maximum row count, and only the byte limit applies.

fields.name: parameterMode
fields.desc: [Experimental] Standard SQL only. Set to POSITIONAL to use positional (?) query parameters or to NAMED to use named (@myparam) query parameters in this query.

fields.name: timeoutMs
fields.desc: [Optional] How long to wait for the query to complete, in milliseconds, before the request times out and returns. Note that this is only a timeout for the request, not the query. If the query takes longer to run than the timeout value, the call returns without any results and with the 'jobComplete' flag set to false. You can call GetQueryResults() to wait for the query to complete and read the results. The default value is 10000 milliseconds (10 seconds).

fields.name: preserveNulls
fields.desc: [Deprecated] This property is deprecated.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: [Required] A query string, following the BigQuery query syntax, of the query to execute. Example: "SELECT count(f1) FROM [myProjectId:myDatasetId.myTableId]".

fields.name: queryParameters
fields.desc: [Experimental] Query parameters for Standard SQL queries.

fields.name: useLegacySql
fields.desc: Specifies whether to use BigQuery's legacy SQL dialect for this query. The default value is true. If set to false, the query will use BigQuery's standard SQL: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/sql-reference/ When useLegacySql is set to false, the values of allowLargeResults and flattenResults are ignored; query will be run as if allowLargeResults is true and flattenResults is false.

fields.name: useQueryCache
fields.desc: [Optional] Whether to look for the result in the query cache. The query cache is a best-effort cache that will be flushed whenever tables in the query are modified. The default value is true.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: A hash of this page of results.

fields.name: kind

fields.name: nextPageToken

fields.name: tables

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: [Experimental] The labels associated with this table. You can use these to organize and group your tables.

fields.name: tableReference
fields.desc: A reference uniquely identifying the table.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of table. Possible values are: TABLE, VIEW.

fields.name: view
fields.desc: Additional details for a view.

fields.name: useLegacySql
fields.desc: True if view is defined in legacy SQL dialect, false if in standard SQL.

fields.name: friendlyName
fields.desc: The user-friendly name for this table.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: An opaque ID of the table

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The resource type.

fields.name: totalItems
fields.desc: The total number of tables in the dataset.

fields.name: expirationMs
fields.desc: [Optional] Number of milliseconds for which to keep the storage for a partition.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Required] The only type supported is DAY, which will generate one partition per day based on data loading time.

fields.name: inlineCode
fields.desc: [Pick one] An inline resource that contains code for a user-defined function (UDF). Providing a inline code resource is equivalent to providing a URI for a file containing the same code.

fields.name: resourceUri
fields.desc: [Pick one] A code resource to load from a Google Cloud Storage URI (gs://bucket/path).

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: [Output-only] A URL that can be used to access the resource again. You can use this URL in Get or Update requests to the resource.

fields.name: access
fields.desc: [Optional] An array of objects that define dataset access for one or more entities. You can set this property when inserting or updating a dataset in order to control who is allowed to access the data. If unspecified at dataset creation time, BigQuery adds default dataset access for the following entities: access.specialGroup: projectReaders; access.role: READER; access.specialGroup: projectWriters; access.role: WRITER; access.specialGroup: projectOwners; access.role: OWNER; access.userByEmail: [dataset creator email]; access.role: OWNER;

fields.name: userByEmail
fields.desc: [Pick one] An email address of a user to grant access to. For example: fred@example.com.

fields.name: view
fields.desc: [Pick one] A view from a different dataset to grant access to. Queries executed against that view will have read access to tables in this dataset. The role field is not required when this field is set. If that view is updated by any user, access to the view needs to be granted again via an update operation.

fields.name: domain
fields.desc: [Pick one] A domain to grant access to. Any users signed in with the domain specified will be granted the specified access. Example: "example.com".

fields.name: groupByEmail
fields.desc: [Pick one] An email address of a Google Group to grant access to.

fields.name: role
fields.desc: [Required] Describes the rights granted to the user specified by the other member of the access object. The following string values are supported: READER, WRITER, OWNER.

fields.name: specialGroup
fields.desc: [Pick one] A special group to grant access to. Possible values include: projectOwners: Owners of the enclosing project. projectReaders: Readers of the enclosing project. projectWriters: Writers of the enclosing project. allAuthenticatedUsers: All authenticated BigQuery users.

fields.name: creationTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] The time when this dataset was created, in milliseconds since the epoch.

fields.name: defaultTableExpirationMs
fields.desc: [Optional] The default lifetime of all tables in the dataset, in milliseconds. The minimum value is 3600000 milliseconds (one hour). Once this property is set, all newly-created tables in the dataset will have an expirationTime property set to the creation time plus the value in this property, and changing the value will only affect new tables, not existing ones. When the expirationTime for a given table is reached, that table will be deleted automatically. If a table's expirationTime is modified or removed before the table expires, or if you provide an explicit expirationTime when creating a table, that value takes precedence over the default expiration time indicated by this property.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: [Optional] A user-friendly description of the dataset.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: [Output-only] A hash of the resource.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: [Output-only] The fully-qualified unique name of the dataset in the format projectId:datasetId. The dataset name without the project name is given in the datasetId field. When creating a new dataset, leave this field blank, and instead specify the datasetId field.

fields.name: lastModifiedTime
fields.desc: [Output-only] The date when this dataset or any of its tables was last modified, in milliseconds since the epoch.

fields.name: datasetReference
fields.desc: [Required] A reference that identifies the dataset.

fields.name: friendlyName
fields.desc: [Optional] A descriptive name for the dataset.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: [Output-only] The resource type.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: [Experimental] The labels associated with this dataset. You can use these to organize and group your datasets. You can set this property when inserting or updating a dataset. See Labeling Datasets for more information.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: [Experimental] The geographic location where the dataset should reside. Possible values include EU and US. The default value is US.

fields.name: datasetId
fields.desc: [Required] A unique ID for this dataset, without the project name. The ID must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), or underscores (_). The maximum length is 1,024 characters.

fields.name: projectId
fields.desc: [Optional] The ID of the project containing this dataset.

fields.name: createDisposition
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies whether the job is allowed to create new tables. The following values are supported: CREATE_IF_NEEDED: If the table does not exist, BigQuery creates the table. CREATE_NEVER: The table must already exist. If it does not, a 'notFound' error is returned in the job result. The default value is CREATE_IF_NEEDED. Creation, truncation and append actions occur as one atomic update upon job completion.

fields.name: destinationTable
fields.desc: [Required] The destination table

fields.name: sourceTable
fields.desc: [Pick one] Source table to copy.

fields.name: sourceTables
fields.desc: [Pick one] Source tables to copy.

fields.name: writeDisposition
fields.desc: [Optional] Specifies the action that occurs if the destination table already exists. The following values are supported: WRITE_TRUNCATE: If the table already exists, BigQuery overwrites the table data. WRITE_APPEND: If the table already exists, BigQuery appends the data to the table. WRITE_EMPTY: If the table already exists and contains data, a 'duplicate' error is returned in the job result. The default value is WRITE_EMPTY. Each action is atomic and only occurs if BigQuery is able to complete the job successfully. Creation, truncation and append actions occur as one atomic update upon job completion.

fields.name: destinationUriFileCounts
fields.desc: [Output-only] Number of files per destination URI or URI pattern specified in the extract configuration. These values will be in the same order as the URIs specified in the 'destinationUris' field.

fields.name: structValues
fields.desc: [Optional] The struct field values, in order of the struct type's declaration.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: [Optional] The value of this value, if a simple scalar type.

fields.name: arrayValues
fields.desc: [Optional] The array values, if this is an array type.

fields.name: printHeader
fields.desc: [Optional] Whether to print out a header row in the results. Default is true.

fields.name: sourceTable
fields.desc: [Required] A reference to the table being exported.

fields.name: compression
fields.desc: [Optional] The compression type to use for exported files. Possible values include GZIP and NONE. The default value is NONE.

fields.name: destinationFormat
fields.desc: [Optional] The exported file format. Possible values include CSV, NEWLINE_DELIMITED_JSON and AVRO. The default value is CSV. Tables with nested or repeated fields cannot be exported as CSV.

fields.name: destinationUri
fields.desc: [Pick one] DEPRECATED: Use destinationUris instead, passing only one URI as necessary. The fully-qualified Google Cloud Storage URI where the extracted table should be written.

fields.name: destinationUris
fields.desc: [Pick one] A list of fully-qualified Google Cloud Storage URIs where the extracted table should be written.

fields.name: fieldDelimiter
fields.desc: [Optional] Delimiter to use between fields in the exported data. Default is ','

fields.name: projectId
fields.desc: [Required] ID of the project. Can be either the numeric ID or the assigned ID of the project.

fields.name: datasetId
fields.desc: [Required] The ID of the dataset containing this table.

fields.name: projectId
fields.desc: [Required] The ID of the project containing this table.

fields.name: tableId
fields.desc: [Required] The ID of the table. The ID must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), or underscores (_). The maximum length is 1,024 characters.

fields.name: fields
fields.desc: Describes the fields in a table.

fields.name: encoding
fields.desc: [Optional] The encoding of the values when the type is not STRING. Acceptable encoding values are: TEXT - indicates values are alphanumeric text strings. BINARY - indicates values are encoded using HBase Bytes.toBytes family of functions. 'encoding' can also be set at the column family level. However, the setting at this level takes precedence if 'encoding' is set at both levels.

fields.name: fieldName
fields.desc: [Optional] If the qualifier is not a valid BigQuery field identifier i.e. does not match [a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_]*, a valid identifier must be provided as the column field name and is used as field name in queries.

fields.name: onlyReadLatest
fields.desc: [Optional] If this is set, only the latest version of value in this column are exposed. 'onlyReadLatest' can also be set at the column family level. However, the setting at this level takes precedence if 'onlyReadLatest' is set at both levels.

fields.name: qualifierEncoded
fields.desc: [Required] Qualifier of the column. Columns in the parent column family that has this exact qualifier are exposed as . field. If the qualifier is valid UTF-8 string, it can be specified in the qualifier_string field. Otherwise, a base-64 encoded value must be set to qualifier_encoded. The column field name is the same as the column qualifier. However, if the qualifier is not a valid BigQuery field identifier i.e. does not match [a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_]*, a valid identifier must be provided as field_name.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: [Optional] The type to convert the value in cells of this column. The values are expected to be encoded using HBase Bytes.toBytes function when using the BINARY encoding value. Following BigQuery types are allowed (case-sensitive) - BYTES STRING INTEGER FLOAT BOOLEAN Default type is BYTES. 'type' can also be set at the column family level. However, the setting at this level takes precedence if 'type' is set at both levels.

fields.name: steps

fields.name: statementType
fields.desc: [Output-only, Experimental] The type of query statement, if valid.

fields.name: totalBytesProcessed

fields.name: billingTier
fields.desc: [Output-only] Billing tier for the job.

fields.name: numDmlAffectedRows
fields.desc: [Output-only, Experimental] The number of rows affected by a DML statement. Present only for DML statements INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE.

fields.name: queryPlan

fields.name: schema

fields.name: totalBytesBilled

fields.name: undeclaredQueryParameters

fields.name: inputFileBytes

fields.name: inputFiles

fields.name: outputBytes
fields.desc: [Output-only] Size of the loaded data in bytes. Note that while a load job is in the running state, this value may change.

methods.name: query
methods.desc: Runs a BigQuery SQL query synchronously and returns query results if the query completes within a specified timeout.

pathParams.name: projectId
pathParams.desc: Project ID of the project billed for the query

methods.name: list
methods.desc: Lists all projects to which you have been granted any project role.

optinalQueryParams.name: maxResults
optinalQueryParams.desc: Maximum number of results to return

optinalQueryParams.name: pageToken
optinalQueryParams.desc: Page token, returned by a previous call, to request the next page of results

methods.name: insertAll
methods.desc: Streams data into BigQuery one record at a time without needing to run a load job. Requires the WRITER dataset role.

pathParams.name: projectId
pathParams.desc: Project ID of the destination table.

pathParams.name: datasetId
pathParams.desc: Dataset ID of the destination table.

pathParams.name: tableId
pathParams.desc: Table ID of the destination table.

methods.name: list
methods.desc: Retrieves table data from a specified set of rows. Requires the READER dataset role.

pathParams.desc: Project ID of the table to read

pathParams.name: datasetId
pathParams.desc: Dataset ID of the table to read

pathParams.name: tableId
pathParams.desc: Table ID of the table to read

optinalQueryParams.name: maxResults
optinalQueryParams.desc: Maximum number of results to return

optinalQueryParams.name: pageToken
optinalQueryParams.desc: Page token, returned by a previous call, identifying the result set

optinalQueryParams.name: startIndex
optinalQueryParams.desc: Zero-based index of the starting row to read

methods.desc: Gets the specified table resource by table ID. This method does not return the data in the table, it only returns the table resource, which describes the structure of this table.

pathParams.name: tableId

methods.name: patch
methods.desc: Updates information in an existing table. The update method replaces the entire table resource, whereas the patch method only replaces fields that are provided in the submitted table resource. This method supports patch semantics.

pathParams.name: projectId
pathParams.desc: Project ID of the table to update

pathParams.name: datasetId
pathParams.desc: Dataset ID of the table to update

pathParams.name: tableId
pathParams.desc: Table ID of the table to update
